**Project type rules:**
- `fullstack` — The project has both a custom frontend and a custom backend.
- `frontend_only` — The project has only a frontend/UI. This includes apps that use a Backend-as-a-Service (BaaS) like Supabase, Firebase, or Convex — the BaaS replaces a custom backend. If the user mentions a BaaS provider or describes only UI/client-side features with no custom server logic, use this type.
- `backend_only` — The project has only a backend: an API, CLI tool, library, or service with no user-facing UI.
- When in doubt, default to `fullstack`.

If the user did not specify a preference, omit that line rather than guessing. Keep feature descriptions concise but complete. Each feature should represent a distinct, testable piece of functionality.
